com.cubeia.space.handler.table
Interface TableHandlerMBean

public interface TableHandlerMBean

This is a small diagnostics interface for the distribution of tables within Firebase. This interface is only used if the statistics level in the server is set to PROFILING.

Author:
Larsan

Method Detail

getAverageCommitTimeMicros

double getAverageCommitTimeMicros()
After events are processed in Firebase their state is replicated across the cluster. This is may be done in a transaction, this method returns the average commit time in micro seconds. If the cache does not use transaction this time represents the time it takes to write data to the socket, ie a "semi-transaction commit".

This value is only calculated if the statistics level in the server is set to PROFILING.

Returns:
The average commit time in micro seconds, or -1

getAverageGameStateObjectSize

double getAverageGameStateObjectSize()
This method returns the average game state size in bytes. The size is calculated from the serialized state.

This value is only calculated if the statistics level in the server is set to PROFILING.

Returns:
The average game state size in bytes, or -1
